            the months of September and October. See Lev 23:39-43.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'He had said that a proclamation should be made throughout their towns
        and in Jerusalem, telling the people to go to the hills to get branches from
        olive, wild olive,[COMMENT[0]] myrtle, palm, and other leafy trees. They
        were to use these branches to make shelters in which they would live during
        the festival, as prescribed in the Law.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'pine; '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: oil tree.
    - title: 
      content: "So the people went out and cut branches and used them to build shelters
        on the roofs of their houses, in their courtyards, in the courtyards of God\u2019s
        Temple, or in the squares just inside the Water Gate and the Ephraim Gate. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So everyone who had returned from captivity lived in these shelters
        during the festival, and they were all filled with great joy! The Israelites
        had not celebrated like this since the days of Joshua[COMMENT[0]] son of
        Nun.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jeshua, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Joshua.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: Ezra read from the Book of the Law of God on each of the seven days
        of the festival. Then on the eighth day they held a solemn assembly, as was
        required by law.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The People Confess Their Sins
      content: 'On October 31[COMMENT[0]] the people assembled again, and this time
        they fasted and dressed in burlap and sprinkled dust on their heads. '
