    - title: 
      content: 'Those of Israelite descent separated themselves from all foreigners
        as they confessed their own sins and the sins of their ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They remained standing in place for three hours[COMMENT[0]] while
        the Book of the Law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God was read
        aloud to them. Then for three more hours they confessed their sins and worshiped
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: for a quarter of a day.
    - title: 
      content: "The Levites\u2014Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah,
        Bani, and Kenani\u2014stood on the stairway of the Levites and cried out
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God with loud voices.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the leaders of the Levites\u2014Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah,
        Sherebiah, Hodiah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah\u2014called out to the people:
        \u201CStand up and praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, for he
        lives from everlasting to everlasting!\u201D Then they prayed:\n\t\u201CMay
        your glorious name be praised! May it be exalted above all blessing and praise!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou alone are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. You made
        the skies and the heavens and all the stars. You made the earth and the seas
        and everything in them. You preserve them all, and the angels of heaven worship
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God, who chose Abram
        and brought him from Ur of the Chaldeans and renamed him Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he had proved himself faithful, you made a covenant with him
        to give him and his descendants the land of the Canaanites, Hittites, Amorites,
        Perizzites, Jebusites, and Girgashites. And you have done what you promised,
        for you are always true to your word.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou saw the misery of our ancestors in Egypt, and you heard
        their cries from beside the Red Sea.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: sea of reeds.
    - title: 
      content: 'You displayed miraculous signs and wonders against Pharaoh, his officials,
        and all his people, for you knew how arrogantly they were treating our ancestors.
        You have a glorious reputation that has never been forgotten. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You divided the sea for your people so they could walk through on
        dry land! And then you hurled their enemies into the depths of the sea. They
        sank like stones beneath the mighty waters. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You led our ancestors by a pillar of cloud during the day and a pillar
        of fire at night so that they could find their way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou came down at Mount Sinai and spoke to them from heaven.
        You gave them regulations and instructions that were just, and decrees and
        commands that were good. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You instructed them concerning your holy Sabbath. And you commanded
        them, through Moses your servant, to obey all your commands, decrees, and
        instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou gave them bread from heaven when they were hungry and water
        from the rock when they were thirsty. You commanded them to go and take possession
        of the land you had sworn to give them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut our ancestors were proud and stubborn, and they paid no
        attention to your commands. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They refused to obey and did not remember the miracles you had done
        for them. Instead, they became stubborn and appointed a leader to take them
        back to their slavery in Egypt.[COMMENT[0]] But you are a God of forgiveness,
        gracious and merciful, slow to become angry, and rich in unfailing love.
        You did not abandon them, '
      comments:
      - number: '9:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: in their rebellion.
    - title: 
      content: "even when they made an idol shaped like a calf and said, \u2018This
        is your god who brought you out of Egypt!\u2019 They committed terrible blasphemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut in your great mercy you did not abandon them to die in
        the wilderness. The pillar of cloud still led them forward by day, and the
        pillar of fire showed them the way through the night. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You sent your good Spirit to instruct them, and you did not stop
        giving them manna from heaven or water for their thirst. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For forty years you sustained them in the wilderness, and they lacked
        nothing. Their clothes did not wear out, and their feet did not swell!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen you helped our ancestors conquer kingdoms and nations,
        and you placed your people in every corner of the land.[COMMENT[0]] They
        took over the land of King Sihon of Heshbon and the land of King Og of Bashan. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:22 '
        contents:
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'You made their descendants as numerous as the stars in the sky and
        brought them into the land you had promised to their ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey went in and took possession of the land. You subdued whole
        nations before them. Even the Canaanites, who inhabited the land, were powerless!
        Your people could deal with these nations and their kings as they pleased. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our ancestors captured fortified cities and fertile land. They took
        over houses full of good things, with cisterns already dug and vineyards
        and olive groves and fruit trees in abundance. So they ate until they were
        full and grew fat and enjoyed themselves in all your blessings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut despite all this, they were disobedient and rebelled against
        you. They turned their backs on your Law, they killed your prophets who warned
        them to return to you, and they committed terrible blasphemies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So you handed them over to their enemies, who made them suffer. But
        in their time of trouble they cried to you, and you heard them from heaven.
        In your great mercy, you sent them liberators who rescued them from their
        enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut as soon as they were at peace, your people again committed
        evil in your sight, and once more you let their enemies conquer them. Yet
        whenever your people turned and cried to you again for help, you listened
        once more from heaven. In your wonderful mercy, you rescued them many times!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou warned them to return to your Law, but they became proud
        and obstinate and disobeyed your commands. They did not follow your regulations,
        by which people will find life if only they obey. They stubbornly turned
        their backs on you and refused to listen. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In your love, you were patient with them for many years. You sent
        your Spirit, who warned them through the prophets. But still they wouldn\u2019t
        listen! So once again you allowed the peoples of the land to conquer them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But in your great mercy, you did not destroy them completely or abandon
        them forever. What a gracious and merciful God you are!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd now, our God, the great and mighty and awesome God, who
        keeps his covenant of unfailing love, do not let all the hardships we have
        suffered seem insignificant to you. Great trouble has come upon us and upon
        our kings and leaders and priests and prophets and ancestors\u2014all of
        your people\u2014from the days when the kings of Assyria first triumphed
        over us until now. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Every time you punished us you were being just. We have sinned greatly,
        and you gave us only what we deserved. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our kings, leaders, priests, and ancestors did not obey your Law
        or listen to the warnings in your commands and laws. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even while they had their own kingdom, they did not serve you, though
        you showered your goodness on them. You gave them a large, fertile land,
        but they refused to turn from their wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo now today we are slaves in the land of plenty that you gave
        our ancestors for their enjoyment! We are slaves here in this good land. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The lush produce of this land piles up in the hands of the kings
        whom you have set over us because of our sins. They have power over us and
        our livestock. We serve them at their pleasure, and we are in great misery.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The People Agree to Obey
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]The people responded, \u201CIn view of all this,[COMMENT[2]]
        we are making a solemn promise and putting it in writing. On this sealed
        document are the names of our leaders and Levites and priests.\u201D"
