    - title: The Vow of the People
      content: "Then the rest of the people\u2014the priests, Levites, gatekeepers,
        singers, Temple servants, and all who had separated themselves from the pagan
        people of the land in order to obey the Law of God, together with their wives,
        sons, daughters, and all who were old enough to understand\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'joined their leaders and bound themselves with an oath. They swore
        a curse on themselves if they failed to obey the Law of God as issued by
        his servant Moses. They solemnly promised to carefully follow all the commands,
        regulations, and decrees of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our Lord:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWe promise not to let our daughters marry the pagan people
        of the land, and not to let our sons marry their daughters.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWe also promise that if the people of the land should bring
        any merchandise or grain to be sold on the Sabbath or on any other holy day,
        we will refuse to buy it. Every seventh year we will let our land rest, and
        we will cancel all debts owed to us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn addition, we promise to obey the command to pay the annual
        Temple tax of one-eighth of an ounce of silver[COMMENT[0]] for the care of
        the Temple of our God. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:32 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'tax of 1/3 of a shekel '
        - ft: '[4 grams].'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'This will provide for the Bread of the Presence; for the regular
        grain offerings and burnt offerings; for the offerings on the Sabbaths, the
        new moon celebrations, and the annual festivals; for the holy offerings;
        and for the sin offerings to make atonement for Israel. It will provide for
        everything necessary for the work of the Temple of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWe have cast sacred lots to determine when\u2014at regular
        times each year\u2014the families of the priests, Levites, and the common
        people should bring wood to God\u2019s Temple to be burned on the altar of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, as is written in the Law.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWe promise to bring the first part of every harvest to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Temple year after year\u2014whether
        it be a crop from the soil or from our fruit trees. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We agree to give God our oldest sons and the firstborn of all our
        herds and flocks, as prescribed in the Law. We will present them to the priests
        who minister in the Temple of our God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We will store the produce in the storerooms of the Temple of our
        God. We will bring the best of our flour and other grain offerings, the best
        of our fruit, and the best of our new wine and olive oil. And we promise
        to bring to the Levites a tenth of everything our land produces, for it is
        the Levites who collect the tithes in all our rural towns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CA priest\u2014a descendant of Aaron\u2014will be with the Levites
        as they receive these tithes. And a tenth of all that is collected as tithes
        will be delivered by the Levites to the Temple of our God and placed in the
        storerooms. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people and the Levites must bring these offerings of grain, new
        wine, and olive oil to the storerooms and place them in the sacred containers
        near the ministering priests, the gatekeepers, and the singers.\n\t\u201CWe
        promise together not to neglect the Temple of our God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The People Occupy Jerusalem
      content: 'The leaders of the people were living in Jerusalem, the holy city.
        A tenth of the people from the other towns of Judah and Benjamin were chosen
        by sacred lots to live there, too, while the rest stayed where they were. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the people commended everyone who volunteered to resettle in
        Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Here is a list of the names of the provincial officials who came
        to live in Jerusalem. (Most of the people, priests, Levites, Temple servants,
        and descendants of Solomon\u2019s servants continued to live in their own
        homes in the various towns of Judah, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but some of the people from Judah and Benjamin resettled in Jerusalem.)\n\tFrom
        the tribe of Judah:\n\tAthaiah son of Uzziah, son of Zechariah, son of Amariah,
        son of Shephatiah, son of Mahalalel, of the family of Perez. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Also Maaseiah son of Baruch, son of Col-hozeh, son of Hazaiah, son
        of Adaiah, son of Joiarib, son of Zechariah, of the family of Shelah.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: son of the Shilonite.
    - title: 
      content: "There were 468 descendants of Perez who lived in Jerusalem\u2014all
        outstanding men.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From the tribe of Benjamin:\n\tSallu son of Meshullam, son of Joed,
        son of Pedaiah, son of Kolaiah, son of Maaseiah, son of Ithiel, son of Jeshaiah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After him were Gabbai and Sallai and a total of 928 relatives. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their chief officer was Joel son of Zicri, who was assisted by Judah
        son of Hassenuah, second-in-command over the city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From the priests:\n\tJedaiah son of Joiarib; Jakin; "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and Seraiah son of Hilkiah, son of Meshullam, son of Zadok, son of
        Meraioth, son of Ahitub, the supervisor of the Temple of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Also 822 of their associates, who worked at the Temple. Also Adaiah
        son of Jeroham, son of Pelaliah, son of Amzi, son of Zechariah, son of Pashhur,
        son of Malkijah, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'along with 242 of his associates, who were heads of their families.
        Also Amashsai son of Azarel, son of Ahzai, son of Meshillemoth, son of Immer, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and 128 of his[COMMENT[0]] outstanding associates. Their chief officer
        was Zabdiel son of Haggedolim.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: their.
    - title: 
      content: "From the Levites:\n\tShemaiah son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam, son
        of Hashabiah, son of Bunni. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Also Shabbethai and Jozabad, who were in charge of the work outside
        the Temple of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Also Mattaniah son of Mica, son of Zabdi, a descendant of Asaph,
        who led in thanksgiving and prayer. Also Bakbukiah, who was Mattaniah\u2019s
        assistant, and Abda son of Shammua, son of Galal, son of Jeduthun. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In all, there were 284 Levites in the holy city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From the gatekeepers:\n\tAkkub, Talmon, and 172 of their associates,
        who guarded the gates.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The other priests, Levites, and the rest of the Israelites lived
        wherever their family inheritance was located in any of the towns of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Temple servants, however, whose leaders were Ziha and Gishpa,
        all lived on the hill of Ophel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The chief officer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi son of Bani,
        son of Hashabiah, son of Mattaniah, son of Mica, a descendant of Asaph, whose
        family served as singers at God\u2019s Temple. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their daily responsibilities were carried out according to the terms
        of a royal command.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pethahiah son of Meshezabel, a descendant of Zerah son of Judah,
        was the royal adviser in all matters of public administration.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As for the surrounding villages with their open fields, some of the
        people of Judah lived in Kiriath-arba with its settlements, Dibon with its
        settlements, and Jekabzeel with its villages. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They also lived in Jeshua, Moladah, Beth-pelet, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hazar-shual, Beersheba with its settlements, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Ziklag, and Meconah with its settlements. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They also lived in En-rimmon, Zorah, Jarmuth, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Zanoah, and Adullam with their surrounding villages. They also lived
        in Lachish with its nearby fields and Azekah with its surrounding villages.
        So the people of Judah were living all the way from Beersheba in the south
        to the valley of Hinnom.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some of the people of Benjamin lived at Geba, Micmash, Aija, and
        Bethel with its settlements. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They also lived in Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lod, Ono, and the Valley of Craftsmen.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:35 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: and Ge-harashim.
    - title: 
      content: Some of the Levites who lived in Judah were sent to live with the
        tribe of Benjamin.
      comments: []
